The licensor grants you a copyright license for the software. You may use the software for any purpose, except for commercial purposes. This license does not grant you any patent rights.

## Noncommercial

This license does not allow you to use the software for commercial purposes. "Commercial purposes" means any use of the software directly or indirectly for direct or indirect financial gain.

## Permissions

You have permission to make copies of the software and distribute those copies, but only under the terms of this license. You also have permission to make changes to the software and distribute your changes, but only under the terms of this license.

## Notices

You must ensure that anyone who gets a copy of any part of the software from you also gets a copy of this license. If you distribute any changes to the software, you must include a notice that you have made changes.

## No Other Rights

This license does not grant any rights except those expressly stated. It does not grant any trademark rights.

## Patent Defense

If you make any claim that the licensor or anyone else has infringed your patent rights by making, using, selling, offering for sale, or importing the software or any part of it, your copyright license for the software is automatically terminated.

